commits Tim has made to `tailwind-nextjs-starter-blog` *after* this SHA
are not yet present here.

## Check what upstream has changed since the last sync

```bash
git fetch upstream
git log 953f052..upstream/master --oneline
# Filter to a specific area:
git log 953f052..upstream/master -- package.json
git diff 953f052..upstream/master -- contentlayer.config.ts
```

## After integrating a new batch from upstream

1. Cherry-pick or manually apply the desired commits.
2. Update the **SHA**, **Date**, and **Subject** lines above with the new
   upstream HEAD watermark.
3. Commit this file change along with the integration work, e.g.
   `chore: sync upstream through <new-sha>`.

